WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:02.300
♪♪

00:02.369 --> 00:04.235
[birds chirping]

00:04.304 --> 00:08.106
[warm laughter]

00:08.175 --> 00:10.341
Care for a carrot
ginger sandwich?

00:10.410 --> 00:11.609
Awww.

00:11.678 --> 00:14.246
You remembered to cut
off the crusts for me.

00:16.783 --> 00:18.050
Of course I did.

00:18.785 --> 00:20.452
I know how you like them.

00:25.292 --> 00:27.692
You really do make
the best finger foods.

00:27.761 --> 00:29.794
[burp]

00:29.863 --> 00:31.329
What do you say?

00:31.398 --> 00:33.231
Excuse me!

00:33.300 --> 00:35.266
Oh! I really can't
take them anywhere.

00:35.335 --> 00:36.468
[giggle]

00:36.537 --> 00:37.536
[crunch]

00:39.273 --> 00:41.173
Can I trouble you for
another sugar cube?

00:43.177 --> 00:46.878
Oh, no. I'm so sorry,
but I seem to be out.

00:46.947 --> 00:49.380
Well, I can just
pop us in some more.

00:49.449 --> 00:50.415
That's all right.

00:50.483 --> 00:52.550
I need to go to
the market anyway.

00:52.619 --> 00:55.553
I have to restock my pantry
for our tea party next week.

00:55.622 --> 00:58.356
Oh, I never realized
how much work you put

00:58.425 --> 01:00.259
into hosting these
tea parties.

01:04.231 --> 01:06.431
Oh, it's really
not that much.

01:06.500 --> 01:07.832
No, no, no, no, no.

01:07.901 --> 01:10.301
I've been taking advantage
of your hospitality

01:10.370 --> 01:11.669
for far too long.

01:11.738 --> 01:13.572
It's high time I do
something about it.

01:14.808 --> 01:18.343
What to do. What to do.

01:18.412 --> 01:21.446
Why don't you host
the next tea party?

01:21.515 --> 01:22.647
I've got it!

01:22.716 --> 01:26.451
Why don't I host the next
tea party at my place?

01:26.520 --> 01:28.353
Hey, that's my idea.

01:28.422 --> 01:29.721
[poof]

01:29.790 --> 01:31.223
Why didn't I see
that coming?

01:32.726 --> 01:34.593
[escaping air hiss]

01:38.565 --> 01:41.866
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:41.935 --> 01:43.801
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

01:43.870 --> 01:45.470
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

01:45.538 --> 01:48.439
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:48.508 --> 01:50.208
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

01:50.276 --> 01:52.777
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:52.846 --> 01:54.579
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

01:54.648 --> 01:56.414
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪ ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:56.483 --> 01:59.117
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

01:59.186 --> 02:01.319
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

02:01.388 --> 02:03.421
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

02:03.490 --> 02:06.758
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:06.827 --> 02:09.328
♪♪

02:14.468 --> 02:15.633
So Fluttershy...

02:15.702 --> 02:18.403
what do you think of
my brilliant,

02:18.472 --> 02:20.672
genius, amazing idea

02:20.741 --> 02:23.175
of having the next tea
party at my place?

02:25.312 --> 02:26.244
[poof]

02:26.313 --> 02:27.278
[running water]

02:27.347 --> 02:28.580
Are you sure?

02:28.648 --> 02:30.648
I wouldn't want you to
go through any trouble.

02:30.717 --> 02:33.752
You, trouble? Never!
I insist.

02:35.455 --> 02:36.821
[poof]

02:36.890 --> 02:38.790
[bleat]

02:40.494 --> 02:41.793
Then count me in.

02:41.862 --> 02:43.761
I'm already looking
forward to it!

02:43.830 --> 02:45.530
Me, too!

02:45.599 --> 02:47.832
I'm so excited; I can't wait.

02:47.901 --> 02:50.602
No, really! I can't.

02:50.671 --> 02:54.539
How about we have the tea
party tomorrow afternoon?

02:54.608 --> 02:56.007
Sounds good to me.

02:56.076 --> 02:59.744
You know, Discord, I've never
been to your house before.

02:59.813 --> 03:03.481
Well, that's OK, because I've
never hosted a tea party before.

03:03.550 --> 03:05.416
[explosion]

03:05.485 --> 03:08.353
Oh? I've never hosted
a tea party before.

03:08.422 --> 03:09.454
So much to do!

03:10.723 --> 03:12.557
Thank you so much for
the tea and nibblies,

03:12.626 --> 03:14.626
but I really must be going.

03:14.695 --> 03:16.327
Uh, Discord...

03:16.396 --> 03:19.431
before you go, would you
mind helping me tidy up?

03:21.702 --> 03:22.700
[poof]

03:22.769 --> 03:23.901
There you go.

03:23.970 --> 03:25.703
Back to normal, just
the way you like it.

03:25.772 --> 03:26.772
See you tomorrow!

03:28.075 --> 03:29.875
I can't wait!

03:32.913 --> 03:36.014
OK, since Fluttershy always
goes out of her way

03:36.083 --> 03:38.449
to host the perfect
tea party for me,

03:38.518 --> 03:40.551
how do I make my
tea party for her

03:40.620 --> 03:42.353
even<i> more</i> perfect?

03:42.422 --> 03:45.890
I'm sorry dearie, were
you talking to me?

03:45.959 --> 03:48.826
Actually, Madam, I'm
talking to myself.

03:48.895 --> 03:50.728
Well, I'm not
talking to you!

03:50.797 --> 03:52.630
It's for Fluttershy.

03:52.699 --> 03:53.831
Oh, all right.

03:53.900 --> 03:55.900
No more holes though.

03:55.969 --> 03:59.570
You have to knock this tea
party out of the park for her.

03:59.639 --> 04:01.806
She was our first
friend, after all.

04:01.875 --> 04:03.775
You don't have to
tell<i> me</i> that.

04:03.844 --> 04:06.678
She gave us a chance
when no other pony would!

04:06.747 --> 04:09.714
She makes us want to be
a better draconequus.

04:09.783 --> 04:12.550
Fluttershy deserves
the best of everything.

04:12.619 --> 04:14.819
Of course. I should get her
the best of everything!

04:14.888 --> 04:16.421
Why didn't I think of that?

04:17.691 --> 04:19.357
Well, are you going
to answer me or not?

04:19.426 --> 04:21.025
Me?

04:21.094 --> 04:22.527
I thought you were
talking to--

04:22.596 --> 04:25.396
--No time!

04:25.465 --> 04:28.667
I'm off to prepare a tea
party worthy of Fluttershy!

04:29.870 --> 04:33.504
[power up]

04:33.573 --> 04:35.373
Excuse me.

04:35.442 --> 04:37.742
Is this where Fluttershy
usually buys her tea?

04:37.811 --> 04:39.644
Why, yes it is.

04:39.713 --> 04:40.745
Oh, wonderful!

04:40.814 --> 04:43.047
I'll be enjoying her
company tomorrow,

04:43.116 --> 04:46.851
so I will be needing your
very best tea, please.

04:46.920 --> 04:49.087
Something especially special.

04:49.156 --> 04:52.690
I'm sure Fluttershy would enjoy
some of our Rosehip green tea.

04:52.759 --> 04:54.659
Oooh. Interesting.

04:54.728 --> 04:58.396
Does it decorate your hips
in roses or turn you green?

04:58.465 --> 05:00.031
Uh, neither?

05:00.100 --> 05:01.966
It just tastes good.

05:02.035 --> 05:03.134
How boring.

05:03.203 --> 05:04.403
Pass.

05:06.506 --> 05:07.438
Hold on!

05:07.507 --> 05:09.640
Ginseng tea.

05:09.709 --> 05:11.442
Now that sounds promising.

05:11.511 --> 05:12.977
What does it sing?

05:13.046 --> 05:16.881
I'm partial to something
upbeat and jazzy.

05:16.950 --> 05:20.418
Again. It's just tasty,
like all of our tea here.

05:20.487 --> 05:24.055
So all this is just
tea you simply drink?

05:24.124 --> 05:25.656
Uh-huh.

05:25.725 --> 05:28.726
Oh! Seems like I got
here just in time.

05:28.795 --> 05:29.727
[snap]

05:29.796 --> 05:31.496
<i>♪ La, la, baloo. ♪</i>

05:31.565 --> 05:33.097
<i>♪ Sha loo ba doo ba dee! ♪</i>

05:33.166 --> 05:34.899
Singing ginseng!

05:34.968 --> 05:36.100
I'll take it!

05:36.169 --> 05:39.137
Are you sure you're
friends with Fluttershy?

05:39.206 --> 05:42.106
You seem so very
different from her.

05:42.175 --> 05:43.775
Well, of course
we're friends.

05:43.844 --> 05:46.744
She gets me and you
obviously do not.

05:46.813 --> 05:49.046
"Are you sure you're
friends with Fluttershy?"

05:49.115 --> 05:50.849
Why, the very nerve.

05:53.053 --> 05:54.653
I'm sorry, do you validate?

05:57.090 --> 05:58.056
Gah!
- Hello.

05:59.759 --> 06:02.093
Uh, can I help you
find something?

06:02.162 --> 06:05.997
Yes you can. Your
finest tea set, please.

06:06.066 --> 06:08.599
I want only the best for
my friend, Fluttershy.

06:08.668 --> 06:11.436
Uh,<i> you're</i> friends
with Fluttershy?

06:13.173 --> 06:16.774
Yes, judge-y clerk pony.

06:16.843 --> 06:18.076
Why is it such a surprise?

06:18.144 --> 06:20.511
Sure, she's on the quieter
side and I'm a bit,

06:20.580 --> 06:22.647
well, more showy.

06:22.716 --> 06:25.149
but I'll have
you know, we're besties.

06:25.218 --> 06:29.487
And that's why I need
the best tea set.

06:29.556 --> 06:31.456
Perhaps then you'd
be interested

06:31.525 --> 06:33.492
in our classic
"Tea for Two" set.

06:36.796 --> 06:38.663
A teapot that just pours tea?

06:38.732 --> 06:40.765
How positively dreadful.

06:40.834 --> 06:43.634
But that's all tea pots
are supposed to do.

06:43.703 --> 06:45.137
Not anymore.

06:48.041 --> 06:49.507
Much better.

06:49.576 --> 06:51.510
Don't wrap it;
I'll walk it home.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.446
[clatter]

06:56.249 --> 06:58.216
Now let's see, I
have the perfect tea

06:58.285 --> 07:00.084
and the perfect tea service.

07:00.153 --> 07:02.653
What else do I need for
the perfect tea party?

07:02.722 --> 07:04.021
Oh!

07:04.090 --> 07:05.524
Decorations, of course!

07:08.061 --> 07:12.530
Good, but not nearly good
enough for Fluttershy.

07:12.599 --> 07:13.197
[snap]

07:13.266 --> 07:14.065
[poof]

07:14.134 --> 07:15.133
Ta da! choo!

07:16.903 --> 07:17.835
Oh, ho ho!

07:17.904 --> 07:19.504
Better.

07:19.573 --> 07:22.507
Oh, I'll need napkins.

07:22.576 --> 07:24.008
I'll simply make them...

07:24.077 --> 07:25.209
I could...

07:25.278 --> 07:26.911
or ...nope.

07:26.980 --> 07:28.646
I've got nothing.

07:28.715 --> 07:30.715
How do I make these better?

07:30.784 --> 07:32.083
What should I do?

07:32.152 --> 07:33.618
Make them...

07:33.687 --> 07:34.820
make them glow.

07:36.122 --> 07:37.989
That's not good
enough for Fluttershy.

07:38.058 --> 07:40.191
Should I make them fly?

07:40.260 --> 07:43.261
Glow, fly and fold!

07:43.330 --> 07:47.632
Glow, fly, fold into
fun shapes perhaps?

07:47.701 --> 07:49.567
Uh, Discord?

07:49.636 --> 07:51.002
Are you OK?

07:51.071 --> 07:52.303
Pinkie Pie?

07:52.372 --> 07:53.604
Just the pony I need.

07:53.673 --> 07:55.273
[poof]
- [snap]

07:55.341 --> 07:58.743
As<i> the</i> party pony and
Fluttershy's close-but-not-best

07:58.812 --> 08:01.212
friend, I need your advice.

08:01.281 --> 08:04.815
I'm hosting a tea party for
her and it has to be perfect.

08:04.884 --> 08:08.185
No, it has to be even
better than perfect!

08:08.254 --> 08:09.754
Oh, Discord.

08:09.823 --> 08:12.790
You're waaaay
over-thinking things.

08:12.859 --> 08:15.126
All you have to do is make
Fluttershy feel comfortable,

08:15.195 --> 08:16.794
which should be
pretty easy for you!

08:16.863 --> 08:17.963
You know her so well!

08:21.034 --> 08:23.768
And that's why you're
the party expert.

08:23.837 --> 08:25.636
Thank you, Pinkie Pie.

08:25.705 --> 08:27.805
I feel so much better now.

08:27.874 --> 08:29.174
Eh, it's what I do.

08:33.747 --> 08:36.347
Excuse me, where can I
find the glowing, flying,

08:36.416 --> 08:37.882
self-folding napkins?

08:42.022 --> 08:43.721
Make Fluttershy
feel comfortable.

08:43.790 --> 08:44.989
Make Fluttershy
feel comfortable.

08:45.058 --> 08:46.157
Comfortable. Comfortable.

08:46.226 --> 08:47.926
Well, I mean that
shouldn't be a problem.

08:55.935 --> 08:58.069
Aie aie aie CHOO!

08:58.138 --> 09:00.771
<i>♪ Ba da, ba da, ba</i>
<i>da, ba daaaaa. ♪</i>

09:00.840 --> 09:03.841
<i>♪ Ba doo, ba doo, ba doobee ♪</i>

09:03.910 --> 09:05.777
Oh, dear. That might
be a problem.

09:09.182 --> 09:10.881
<i>♪ La la laa. ♪</i>

09:10.950 --> 09:12.617
<i>♪ La la la la la laa. ♪</i>

09:12.686 --> 09:14.185
Maybe it's not as
bad as I think.

09:14.254 --> 09:16.120
Maybe Fluttershy
would be comfortable

09:16.189 --> 09:18.055
having a tea party here.

09:18.124 --> 09:20.057
<i>♪ Ba da, ba da, ba</i>
<i>da, ba daaaaa. ♪</i>

09:20.126 --> 09:23.094
<i>♪ Ba doo, ba doo, ba doobee ♪</i>

09:23.163 --> 09:25.396
Maybe I just need another
set of eyes on this.

09:25.465 --> 09:26.664
What do you think?

09:26.733 --> 09:27.765
[poof]

09:27.834 --> 09:29.033
[gasp]

09:29.102 --> 09:30.267
That bad?

09:30.336 --> 09:31.802
No... worse!

09:31.871 --> 09:33.704
Fluttershy would never
be comfortable here.

09:33.773 --> 09:36.407
What have you done?

09:36.476 --> 09:39.710
I was trying to make the tea
party different and special...

09:39.779 --> 09:41.112
like me.

09:41.180 --> 09:44.949
But all I did was make it
chaotic and weird... like me.

09:45.018 --> 09:48.386
What if those ponies at the tea
shop and china shop were right?

09:48.455 --> 09:51.222
What if Fluttershy sees how
crazy this place is

09:51.291 --> 09:53.691
and realizes how
different we are

09:53.760 --> 09:55.826
and then doesn't
want to be friends anymore?

09:55.895 --> 09:58.429
[gasping]

09:58.498 --> 10:01.065
Relax. We can fix this.

10:01.134 --> 10:02.800
Time to call in
the team.

10:02.869 --> 10:07.138
♪♪

10:07.207 --> 10:10.074
OK, chief. What's the plan?

10:10.143 --> 10:12.410
What to do, what to do?
What to do?

10:12.479 --> 10:14.979
Oh! Got it!

10:15.048 --> 10:17.682
We know Fluttershy and
we know what she likes.

10:17.751 --> 10:20.985
First of all, we need to get
rid of all the new stuff.

10:21.054 --> 10:21.753
You heard him.

10:21.821 --> 10:23.220
Strike the new stuff!

10:23.289 --> 10:26.291
♪♪

10:46.346 --> 10:49.413
<i>♪ Ba doo, ba doo, ba doobee ♪</i>

10:49.482 --> 10:51.916
Piñatas hate bats.

10:51.985 --> 10:54.285
Enjoy your all-expense-paid
trip around Equestria!

10:56.523 --> 10:59.424
Well, done everybody, but
there's still more work to do.

11:00.927 --> 11:01.826
[groan]

11:01.895 --> 11:03.828
[complaining]

11:03.897 --> 11:06.464
We need to make this place
more Fluttershy and less...

11:06.533 --> 11:08.799
well, me.

11:08.868 --> 11:10.801
One thing I know
about my dear friend

11:10.870 --> 11:13.270
is that she loves
comfy chairs...

11:13.339 --> 11:15.006
But not on the ceiling.

11:16.943 --> 11:20.311
And I'm almost certain she likes
stairs that lead somewhere.

11:30.290 --> 11:31.889
And although we've
never discussed it,

11:31.958 --> 11:34.092
I'm pretty sure
Fluttershy likes gravity.

11:37.030 --> 11:40.464
OK fellas, this is a good
start, but stand back.

11:40.533 --> 11:42.333
Let me show you how it's done.

11:42.402 --> 11:44.268
We just need some of this...

11:44.337 --> 11:45.369
[snap]

11:45.438 --> 11:46.303
And a little of that--

11:46.372 --> 11:47.204
[snap]

11:47.273 --> 11:48.273
[poof]

11:49.075 --> 11:50.007
[snap]

11:50.076 --> 11:50.741
[poof]

11:50.810 --> 11:52.476
Oooooohh. Aaaaaaah.

11:52.545 --> 11:53.844
Wow!

11:53.913 --> 11:55.212
And a whole lot
of those!

11:55.281 --> 11:56.213
[snap]

11:56.282 --> 11:57.282
[poof]

11:57.484 --> 11:58.415
[snap]

11:58.484 --> 11:59.416
[poof]

11:59.485 --> 12:00.417
[snap]

12:00.486 --> 12:01.418
[poof]

12:01.487 --> 12:02.487
Whew!

12:04.290 --> 12:05.456
How boring.

12:05.525 --> 12:06.891
I mean, normal.

12:06.960 --> 12:07.992
Thank you.

12:08.061 --> 12:09.360
Good job.

12:09.429 --> 12:11.929
The window treatments are
perfectly unexceptional.

12:11.998 --> 12:14.064
But we're not done yet.

12:14.133 --> 12:15.199
You don't mean...

12:15.268 --> 12:17.101
Mhmm!

12:17.170 --> 12:19.203
Make-over!

12:19.272 --> 12:22.506
♪♪

12:22.575 --> 12:23.775
Hating it.

12:28.381 --> 12:29.781
Hating it.

12:33.586 --> 12:34.919
Hating it.

12:37.657 --> 12:40.458
Hating ... how
much I love it!

12:43.062 --> 12:46.064
♪♪

12:51.638 --> 12:52.903
[buzzing]

12:52.972 --> 12:53.571
Agh!

12:53.640 --> 12:54.806
♪♪

12:56.376 --> 12:59.109
OK, let's give these
conversation cards a whirl.

12:59.178 --> 13:00.945
Ahem.

13:01.014 --> 13:03.948
It is very nice
to see you today.

13:06.586 --> 13:09.386
Have you read any
good books lately?

13:09.455 --> 13:12.991
Your garden looks
positively lovely.

13:17.196 --> 13:18.263
Right on!
- Great!

13:20.099 --> 13:22.066
Oh, quite strange, for
the first time in my life,

13:22.135 --> 13:24.268
I don't feel quite strange.

13:24.337 --> 13:28.172
In fact, I feel
completely normal.

13:28.241 --> 13:32.176
Everything is finally
perfect for Fluttershy.

13:32.245 --> 13:33.978
[clock chimes]

13:34.047 --> 13:35.613
And just in time.

13:35.682 --> 13:36.513
[snap]

13:36.582 --> 13:37.948
[poof]

13:38.017 --> 13:42.253
Discord, I'm so excited to
finally see where you live.

13:42.322 --> 13:43.988
Greetings, friend.

13:44.057 --> 13:45.557
Please do come in.

13:47.193 --> 13:50.294
I can't wait to see how...oh.

13:50.363 --> 13:54.265
[clock ticking]

13:54.334 --> 13:55.566
Is something amiss?

13:55.635 --> 13:57.434
Um. No, no,
not at all.

13:57.503 --> 13:59.403
It's just not
what I expected.

13:59.472 --> 14:02.039
It's quite... lovely.

14:02.108 --> 14:04.475
Please, have a seat.

14:04.544 --> 14:05.609
Where is it?

14:05.678 --> 14:07.178
Right here.

14:08.448 --> 14:10.247
Oh.

14:10.316 --> 14:12.950
I think you'll be quite
pleased with the green tea

14:13.019 --> 14:15.185
I've selected for us today.

14:15.254 --> 14:18.188
Oooh! Does it actually
turn us green?

14:18.257 --> 14:20.491
Is it really envious
of the other teas?

14:20.560 --> 14:22.459
What's it do?
What's it do?

14:22.528 --> 14:25.129
Well... it tastes
delicious.

14:25.198 --> 14:27.065
Oh. OK.

14:30.636 --> 14:33.137
What particularly nice
weather we're having.

14:33.206 --> 14:35.607
Yes. Yes we are.

14:38.444 --> 14:41.111
It did rain the
other day, however.

14:41.180 --> 14:42.680
Uh-huh.

14:42.749 --> 14:46.317
But the weather today
is particularly nice...

14:46.386 --> 14:48.953
as I previously
mentioned.

14:51.257 --> 14:53.557
Would you care for
some milk toast?

14:53.626 --> 14:57.594
Uh, Discord you don't
seem to be yourself today.

14:57.663 --> 14:59.596
Are you feeling
all right?

14:59.665 --> 15:01.532
What ever do you mean?

15:01.601 --> 15:05.502
Well, it's just...
what you're wearing.

15:05.571 --> 15:07.404
And also, what
you're saying.

15:07.473 --> 15:09.273
And also the way
you're saying it.

15:09.342 --> 15:11.475
And um, pretty much
everything else.

15:11.544 --> 15:13.310
Oh, dear Fluttershy.
Worry not.

15:13.379 --> 15:15.245
I can assure you that
for the first time,

15:15.314 --> 15:17.381
I'm feeling perfectly normal.

15:17.450 --> 15:19.483
Now let me top you off.

15:19.552 --> 15:20.751
Whoops!

15:20.820 --> 15:22.252
Butter fingers.

15:22.321 --> 15:23.688
How embarrassing.

15:25.391 --> 15:27.158
Uh...what's going on?

15:30.163 --> 15:32.596
I have no idea.

15:32.665 --> 15:36.000
Discord! You're
starting to fade away!

15:36.069 --> 15:39.069
Oh. You don't say.

15:39.138 --> 15:41.238
Have you read any
good books lately?

15:41.307 --> 15:43.073
[weak chuckle]

15:43.142 --> 15:44.442
<i>♪ [horror sting] ♪</i>

15:47.080 --> 15:49.013
♪♪

15:49.082 --> 15:49.948
Huh!

15:50.850 --> 15:51.816
Have you tried
the scones?

15:51.885 --> 15:54.051
They're positively
delectable.

15:54.120 --> 15:56.353
The secret is in
the extra butter.

15:56.422 --> 15:58.288
What is wrong with you?

15:58.357 --> 16:02.192
You're acting so "normal"
which is not so normal for you!

16:02.261 --> 16:03.794
What ever do you mean?

16:03.863 --> 16:06.563
This is just me being me.

16:06.632 --> 16:08.332
No, it's not!

16:08.401 --> 16:11.468
It's you being like
everypony else!

16:11.537 --> 16:12.537
[gasp]

16:15.341 --> 16:16.507
Eeep!

16:16.576 --> 16:18.443
The more you do it the
more you fade away!

16:19.479 --> 16:21.245
Of course!

16:21.314 --> 16:23.247
You're a creature of
pure chaos!

16:23.316 --> 16:25.316
Being normal is
destroying you!

16:26.385 --> 16:28.452
Oh, haha, how interesting.

16:28.521 --> 16:31.289
That reminds me of something I
heard at the market today.

16:33.359 --> 16:35.192
STOP IT! Please.

16:35.261 --> 16:37.795
You need to go back to being
your not-normal normal self!

16:37.864 --> 16:41.065
Quick, Discord do something
chaotic before it's too late!

16:41.134 --> 16:42.633
Please!

16:42.702 --> 16:44.168
Do something chaotic?

16:44.237 --> 16:45.670
I'll try.

16:47.173 --> 16:50.507
Ohh, that's not good.

16:50.576 --> 16:52.709
Then I guess it's up to me.

16:52.778 --> 16:54.511
Uh, OK. All right.

16:54.580 --> 16:55.512
How about...?

16:55.581 --> 16:57.414
[panicked gasps]

16:57.483 --> 16:58.415
[clink]

16:58.484 --> 16:59.683
Oh, no.

16:59.752 --> 17:01.652
I tipped over that cup.

17:01.721 --> 17:04.354
That's pretty chaotic, right?

17:04.423 --> 17:06.223
[yawn]

17:06.292 --> 17:07.325
What if I...?

17:08.694 --> 17:10.694
[chomping]

17:10.763 --> 17:13.097
Oh, my! Talking with food
in my mouth

17:13.166 --> 17:17.602
after taking a bite from every
sandwich... how wacky!

17:19.172 --> 17:20.271
Doing anything for ya?

17:22.208 --> 17:24.308
OK. Hmmm.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.276
Maybe I need to start
thinking like you.

17:26.345 --> 17:29.446
What would Discord do?

17:29.515 --> 17:32.182
Well, I guess, he'd probably
make another version of himself

17:32.251 --> 17:33.651
to bounce ideas off of.

17:36.222 --> 17:37.287
But one wouldn't be enough.

17:37.356 --> 17:38.856
He'd need more. Way more.

17:38.925 --> 17:42.126
♪♪

17:46.799 --> 17:49.700
Hey there, Fluttershys, any
ideas on how to Discord-up

17:49.769 --> 17:51.468
this tea party?

17:51.537 --> 17:53.670
Hi Fluttershy,
thanks for asking!

17:53.739 --> 17:56.140
First of all, you gotta
redecorate this place!

17:56.209 --> 17:58.809
I mean this is where Discord
lives! And you're telling me

17:58.878 --> 18:01.712
there aren't any stairs
that lead to nowhere?

18:01.781 --> 18:03.247
On it!

18:03.316 --> 18:06.317
♪♪

18:16.862 --> 18:19.730
Better, but it still
needs something.

18:23.769 --> 18:25.470
Now that's more like it!

18:26.672 --> 18:28.539
[whoosh]

18:28.608 --> 18:29.607
It's working!

18:30.676 --> 18:32.209
OK, what else?

18:32.278 --> 18:33.343
Furniture on the ground?

18:33.412 --> 18:34.511
So predictable!

18:34.580 --> 18:37.281
Let's put them where
they don't belong.

18:37.350 --> 18:38.382
[tap tap]

18:38.451 --> 18:39.249
♪♪

18:39.318 --> 18:40.318
[tap tap]

18:40.553 --> 18:42.687
[tap tap]

18:45.891 --> 18:47.357
[whoosh]

18:47.426 --> 18:49.893
And he'd have a chaise lounge
that would actually chase you

18:49.962 --> 18:51.795
because he's funny like that.

18:51.864 --> 18:53.264
I bet you can't catch me!

18:54.600 --> 18:56.500
[chuckle]

18:56.569 --> 18:57.501
[snap]

18:57.570 --> 18:58.502
[happy gasp]

18:58.571 --> 18:59.703
Ha ha ha ha!

18:59.772 --> 19:04.374
♪♪

19:04.443 --> 19:06.843
Oh, and Discord would have
a special kind of tea,

19:06.912 --> 19:09.580
like a ginseng that
could really sing!

19:09.649 --> 19:11.882
I would! I would!

19:11.951 --> 19:13.151
[snap]

19:14.187 --> 19:15.153
<i>♪ La, la, la, la! ♪</i>

19:15.221 --> 19:17.688
<i>♪ Lala lala la la! ♪</i>

19:17.757 --> 19:20.224
And he'd serve it
on a floating table!

19:20.293 --> 19:21.459
We've never talked about it,

19:21.528 --> 19:23.627
but I'm pretty sure
Discord hates gravity.

19:23.696 --> 19:26.396
I do! Who wants to be
tethered to the ground

19:26.465 --> 19:28.432
when you can do this?

19:28.501 --> 19:29.667
[snap]

19:29.736 --> 19:34.605
Now this is exactly
what I was hoping for!

19:34.674 --> 19:37.274
This is what you
were hoping for?

19:37.343 --> 19:40.644
But this is the complete
opposite of your tea parties.

19:40.713 --> 19:43.280
I wouldn't expect you to throw
a tea party the way I would!

19:43.349 --> 19:44.348
We're different.

19:45.518 --> 19:46.951
I know.

19:47.019 --> 19:49.886
I was afraid that if you saw
exactly how different we are,

19:49.955 --> 19:51.788
you wouldn't want to
be friends anymore!

19:51.857 --> 19:53.557
What?

19:53.626 --> 19:55.826
Why would you ever
think that?

19:55.895 --> 20:01.031
Because... you and I don't
make sense to anypony else.

20:01.100 --> 20:04.434
That may be true, but
we make sense to me.

20:04.503 --> 20:06.703
I never would have thought
to make singing ginseng

20:06.772 --> 20:08.839
before I met you.

20:08.908 --> 20:11.475
But you've opened me up to so
many more possibilities

20:11.544 --> 20:13.543
and impossibilities!

20:13.612 --> 20:15.912
So I guess what I'm
trying to say is,

20:15.981 --> 20:19.349
I like you<i> because</i> you're
so different from me.

20:19.418 --> 20:20.751
You do?

20:20.820 --> 20:22.953
Of course I do, silly.

20:23.022 --> 20:26.990
Besides, what's Discord
without a little chaos?

20:27.059 --> 20:31.061
Well, in that case, I certainly
don't need to be wearing this.

20:31.130 --> 20:32.462
[rip]

20:32.531 --> 20:33.497
Whoops.

20:33.565 --> 20:36.533
I forgot that I
still had this on.

20:36.602 --> 20:37.434
[poof]

20:37.503 --> 20:38.535
[giggle]

20:38.604 --> 20:40.671
Now, about that tea party...

20:40.740 --> 20:42.472
♪♪

20:42.541 --> 20:45.909
You know, your garden
really is looking lovely.

20:45.978 --> 20:48.812
Why, thank you for noticing.

20:48.881 --> 20:51.449
I also couldn't help but
notice that you need a refill.

20:54.387 --> 20:55.720
Aie! Achoo!

20:57.390 --> 20:58.889
Gesundheit!

20:58.958 --> 21:01.391
It really is nice
having you here.

21:01.460 --> 21:03.160
I'm happy to be here.

21:03.228 --> 21:07.664
And I really do like your
place...<i> because</i> it's so you.

21:07.733 --> 21:10.100
Why thank you, Fluttershy.

21:10.169 --> 21:12.035
Now, how about we
try some of those

21:12.104 --> 21:13.804
delicious-looking
sandwiches?

21:15.841 --> 21:16.773
Ha ho!

21:16.842 --> 21:17.975
You read my mind.

21:19.745 --> 21:21.479
[giggles]

21:24.150 --> 21:25.882
<i>♪ La, la, la, la! ♪</i>

21:25.951 --> 21:28.051
<i>♪ Lala lala la la! ♪</i>

21:28.120 --> 21:31.688
<i>[giggles]</i>

21:31.757 --> 21:32.757
Yahoo!
